EXAMPLE 3
In Example 3, the five sets of the Wheatstone bridge resistor-adjustment test described in Example 1 were relabeled as Sets 3-1, 3-2, 3-3, 3-4 and 3-5. A formulated sequential sixth set, Set 3-6, was added to this group of sets to form a new series. Set 3-6 had more extreme swings than could be practically produced on the Wheatstone bridge apparatus. The devised readings and mean value for Set 3-6 are shown in Table 7.

